commText: Head and Abhishek Sharma are at the crease. Head is on strike. Chahar will open the attack
Chahar to Head, FOUR, and Head is away. A short of length delivery outside off, angling away from Head who cuts wide of point and cover-point
Chahar to Head, no run, back of a length just outside off, Head punches to cover-point
Chahar to Head, 1 run, short of length just outside off, Head whips it to deep mid-wicket and there is a fielder there
Chahar to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, ooh! This swung back in, full on the stumps, clipped wide of mid-on and Abhishek Sharma is away too
Chahar to Head, 1 run, back of a length on the stumps, Head makes room to punch, thick inside-edge runs down to backward square leg
Chahar to Abhishek Sharma, no run, fullish and angling away from Abhishek Sharma, outside off, left alone and that is a rarity, to see the left-hander leave one
Tushar Deshpande, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Tushar Deshpande to Head, SIX, Tushar Deshpande with a jogging run-up, runs in and delivers a full delivery outside the leg-stump, easy for Head who flicks over deep square leg and it's six
Tushar Deshpande to Head, 1 run, full outside off, Head slices the square drive, was in the air, but cover-point is back, so just one

Tushar Deshpande to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, now Abhishek Sharma gets into the act. Full and around off, no mercy as Abhishek Sharma swings it a mile into the deep mid-wicket stands and he did not get it off the middle too
Tushar Deshpande to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, short of length outside off, tapped in front of cover
Tushar Deshpande to Head, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Tushar Deshpande to Head, out Caught by Mitchell!! Head holes out. Full slower ball and wide outside off, he goes on one knee and carves it, does not get the elevation or power to clear deep point and Mitchell isn't dropping them. Massive wicket for CSK. Head c Mitchell b Tushar Deshpande 13(7) [4s-1 6s-1]
SRH bring in their impact player - Anmolpreet Singh in, Natarajan out.
Anmolpreet Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Tushar Deshpande to Anmolpreet Singh, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Tushar Deshpande to Anmolpreet Singh, out Caught by Moeen Ali!! Two in two. Full outswinger on the stumps, late movement away, Anmolpreet Singh closes the face of the bat too early and the thick leading-edge lobs to extra-cover and Mo has the simplest of catches. The impact sub goes for a golden duck. Tushar Deshpande is thrilled. Anmolpreet Singh c Moeen Ali b Tushar Deshpande 0(1)
Aiden Markram, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Chahar to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, good length on middle, flicked through the vacant mid-wicket
Chahar to Markram, FOUR, Markram is away with a fine shot. A short of length delivery just outside off, he punches wide of cover-point to his left, runs away
Chahar to Markram, FOUR, poor ball, short and wide outside off, cut over backward point and that's consecutive fours for Markram
Chahar to Markram, 1 run, short of length on off, flicked wide of mid-wicket
Chahar to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, slower short ball at Abhishek Sharma who gloves the pull, was it on to the helmet? Or to the body, anyway dribbles from there to short fine-leg
Chahar to Markram, 1 run, short of length on leg-stump, tucked wide of short fine-leg for one
Tushar Deshpande to Markram, 1 run, hat-trick ball and it's short of length and angling into middle, Markram on the defence gets a thick leading-edge that rolls to cover
Tushar Deshpande to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, Abhishek Sharma mistimes the cut to cover who's deep, easy single
Tushar Deshpande to Markram, 1 run, short of length on off, again a bit of hold as Markram punches and has to check his shot, in the air but no silly mid-off
Tushar Deshpande to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, smashed. On a back of a length just outside off, slapped straight down the ground and that's dismissive
Tushar Deshpande to Abhishek Sharma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Tushar Deshpande to Abhishek Sharma, out Caught by Mitchell!! Abhishek Sharma too finds deep point and Tushar Deshpande has three. Looked like the slower short ball outside off, slashed and Mitchell tracks back to take it. A bit more elevation and Abhishek Sharma would have got six. SRH fans are shell-shocked. Abhishek Sharma c Mitchell b Tushar Deshpande 15(9) [4s-1 6s-1]
Nitish Reddy, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Tushar Deshpande to Nitish Reddy, 2 runs, short of length outside off, punched through cover-point and Nitish Reddy takes on Jadeja in the deep to come back for two

Excellent from CSK to have deep point and using the longer side to get both Head and Abhishek. Tushar Deshpande with innocuous deliveries both to get wickets but he changed the pace and the ploy to have that fielder back worked.
Chahar to Markram, no run, full outside off, Markram gets forward to drive well but picks out cover-point
Chahar to Markram, 1 run, fullish outside off, slashed hard and straight to deep point
Chahar to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, short at Nitish Reddy who is rushed on the shot, miscues it but there's no mid-wicket
Chahar to Markram, 1 run, short of length outside off, Markram looks to flat-bat the cut, mistimes to mid-off for a single
Chahar to Nitish Reddy, no run, short of length outside off, Nitish Reddy slashes and misses, was on his tiptoes to play that
Chahar to Nitish Reddy, no run, short of length and nips back in a tad, foils Nitish Reddy's attempt to punch, thick inside-edge rolls back down the pitch
Mustafizur Rahman, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Mustafizur to Markram, FOUR, full and wide outside off, angling away from Markram who drives and it's skewed off the thickish outside half, through backward point and no chance for Jadeja at sweeper cover
Mustafizur to Markram, no run, full on the stumps, driven straight to the fielder at extra-cover
Tushar Deshpande in Powerplay this IPL \nBefore today: One wkts in 14 overs (ER: 7.92) \nThis match: Three wkts in 2 overs (ER: 11.50)
Three wickets within the PP this season 3/14 - Trent Boult vs MI, Wankhede 3/15 - Sandeep Warrier vs DC, Delhi 3/23 - T Deshpande vs SRH, Chennai*
Mustafizur to Markram, 1 run, slower ball full outside off, Markram reaches for it and drives to the off-side to take one
Mustafizur to Nitish Reddy, 2 runs, full on the pads, flicked wide of deep mid-wicket for two
Mustafizur to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter on the stumps, holds and Nitish Reddy pushes at it, thick outside half and it rolls to cover
Mustafizur to Markram, no run, slower ball off-cutter on a back of a length on the stumps, Markram is surprised as it holds and jumps at it, checks the flick, rolls back down the pitch
Powerplay summary -- Deshpande takes three-for with new ball -- Head falls cheaply for 13 (1.5) -- Impact sub Anmolpreet goes for a golden duck (1.6) -- Abhishek is caught at deep point for 15 (3.5)
Ravindra Jadeja, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Jadeja to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, tossed up full on the stumps, Nitish Reddy gets forward to drive wide of cover
Jadeja to Markram, 1 run, full on the stumps, Markram gets forward to drive to long-off
Jadeja to Nitish Reddy, 2 runs, flighted delivery full outside off, slapped wide of deep extra-cover and Rizvi gets across and cuts it off
Jadeja to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, back of a length on off, whipped to long-on
Second lowest powerplay score for SRH this IPL after 40/3 runs against PBKS at Mullanpur.
Jadeja to Markram, no run, flat and fast just outside off, Markram cuts but finds Mo at backward point
Jadeja to Markram, 1 run, yet another dart, back of a length on the stumps, flicked to deep mid-wicket
Shardul Thakur, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Thakur to Markram, FOUR, poor ball to start with. Back of a length delivery straying down leg, slower ball, Markram looks to pull and drags it off a thick under-edge past short fine
Thakur to Markram, no ball, oh dear. An attempted slower ball slips out of the hand and ends up as a beamer over the head. Markram ducks under it
Thakur to Markram, 1 run, just a single off the free hit as Thakur bowls a good slower bouncer. It climbs on Markram who goes hard on the pull and miscues it to long-on
Thakur to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, 133kph length ball wide of off, Reddy looks to cut but mistimes it wide of point
Thakur to Markram, 1 run, length ball outside off, Markram slaps it to sweeper cover
Thakur to Nitish Reddy, 2 runs, back of a length on off, Reddy hangs back and tucks it through midwicket. Nicely judged two for him
Thakur to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, back of a length delivery just outside off, Reddy hangs back, opens the face and steers it to deep third
10th No-ball by CSK bowlers is the most by a team this season. Whereas PBKS has not bowled a single no-ball this season so far.
Jadeja to Nitish Reddy, no run, full delivery on off, 102.9kph, Reddy shuffles across looking to work it to long-on but Jadeja cuts it off to his right
Jadeja to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, 101.7kph, flat on off, back of a length, Reddy shuffles across and tucks it to long-on
CSK's spinners have picked just 8 wickets in 8 matches - joint least by a team with MI and they have conceded runs at 7.60 - lowest among all the teams.
Jadeja to Markram, no run, Markram backs away too far and Jadeja fires it wide outside off. Markram looks to cut but misses
Jadeja to Markram, 1 run, 99.9kph, fired in on off, Markram gets forward and drives to long-off
Jadeja to Nitish Reddy, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Jadeja to Nitish Reddy, out Caught by Dhoni!! Almost a bouncer from Jadeja at 104kph, takes Reddy by surprise and sends him packing! He gets a thick top-edge while going for the pull shot, and it goes high in the air. Dhoni takes it comfortably. Jadeja has a big smile on his face, having outfoxed Reddy with this variation. He banged it in and got it to rise above the chest. Imagine his delight at bouncing someone out. Nitish Reddy c Dhoni b Jadeja 15(15)
Timeout! Reddy and Markram were doing a decent job of rebuilding, but that partnership is broken now. Long road ahead for SRH.
Heinrich Klaasen, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Jadeja to Klaasen, 1 run, full delivery on off, Klaasen gets forward and pushes wide of cover
Mustafizur Rahman [1.0-0-8-0] is back into the attack
Mustafizur to Klaasen, no run, length ball on leg stump, 135kph, and Klaasen defends from the crease
Mustafizur to Klaasen, no run, back of a length outside off, Klaasen looks to cut but chops it off a thick under-edge down the pitch
Mustafizur to Klaasen, 1 run, short of length at the body, slower one, and Klaasen pulls it gently to deep midwicket
Mustafizur to Markram, 1 run, slower bouncer on off, pulled to deep midwicket
Mustafizur to Klaasen, 1 run, slower one outside off, length ball, Klaasen cuts wide of extra cover who makes a diving stop
Mustafizur to Markram, 2 runs, another slower short ball, Markram miscues the pull in the air but it lands safely in the midwicket region. He scampers back for two
Matheesha Pathirana, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Pathirana to Klaasen, 1 run, back of a length outside off, off-pace at 132kph, Klaasen hangs back and dabs it in front of the keeper
Pathirana to Markram, 1 run, full delivery on off, driven to long-on
Pathirana to Klaasen, wide, slower short ball down leg, Klaasen looks to pull but misses
Pathirana to Klaasen, 2 runs, full on the pads, 129kph, and Klaasen flicks it nicely through midwicket for a couple
Pathirana to Klaasen, 1 run, short of length around off, slower one, and Klaasen pulls to deep backward square
Pathirana to Markram, wide, slower full toss down leg, Markram swings and misses
Pathirana to Markram, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Pathirana to Markram, out Bowled!! Middle stump out of the ground! Markram is left flummoxed by a Pathirana special. A 147kph yorker on the stumps, bends in slightly, Markram goes for a forceful drive and is beaten comprehensively as it crashes into middle. Sunrisers in tatters. Markram b Pathirana 32(26) [4s-4]
Abdul Samad, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Pathirana to Abdul Samad, 1 run, full outside off, 146.8kph, Samad gets forward and mistimes the drive to short cover
Ravindra Jadeja [2.0-0-9-1] is back into the attack
Jadeja to Abdul Samad, 1 run, length ball on the pads, Samad clips it through square leg
The ball is being changed. Klaasen having a chat with the umpires to understand the reason for it. There's plenty of dew on the outfield, so CSK will be happy no doubt.
SRH's scores at fall of 5th wicket in last two games \n69 vs RCB, Hyderabad \n85 vs CSK, Chennai*
Jadeja to Klaasen, no run, flat length ball on off, Klaasen leans back and punches to cover
Jadeja to Klaasen, SIX, Klaasen will smash anything on that length all day. Full in the slot on middle, he clears the front leg and launches it over long-off
Jadeja to Klaasen, 1 run, fired in full on the pads, Klaasen flicks through midwicket
Jadeja to Abdul Samad, 1 run, flat on middle, back of a length, Samad hangs back and punches to long-on

Jadeja to Klaasen, no run, 101.8kph length ball sliding in on leg, Klaasen tucks it to the right of Jadeja who runs across and tries stopping it with his boot. He ends up kicking it away further and has to give chase. But Klaasen remains cautious and turns down the single
Shardul Thakur [1.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack
Thakur to Abdul Samad, FOUR, back of a length outside off, plenty of width and Samad slaps it through extra cover. It races away to the fence
Thakur to Abdul Samad, no run, full ball just outside off, Samad drills it in the air it falls just short of Moeen at mid-off
Thakur to Abdul Samad, 1 run, back of a length at the stumps, Samad mistimes the pull through midwicket
Thakur to Klaasen, 1 run, back of a length outside off, Klaasen cuts to deep backward point

Thakur to Abdul Samad, no run, did that carry to Dhoni? Fuller than a length outside off, Samad looks to drive but edges it to the right of the keeper. Might have just carried. Dhoni dives across one-handed and fails to get his fingers under it
Thakur to Abdul Samad, 1 run, short of length outside off, Samad looks to cut and chops it to point
Jadeja to Abdul Samad, no run, length ball darted in outside off, Samad looks to cut but is beaten
Jadeja to Abdul Samad, 1 run, length ball outside off, Samad slaps it hard to backward point and a misfield from Moeen gives him a single
Jadeja to Klaasen, no run, Klaasen backs away to the leg-side and Jadeja smartly fires it wide outside off. Klaasen ends up leaving it alone
Jadeja to Klaasen, 1 run, 104.5kph, flat and wide outside off, back of a length. Klaasen reaches out and mistimes the cut to extra cover
Jadeja to Abdul Samad, 1 run, 107.3kph, darted in outside off, back of a length, and Samad cuts to deep point
Jadeja to Klaasen, 1 run, length ball darted in outside off, Klaasen punches off the back foot wide of cover. Jadeja finishes with 1/22
Thakur to Klaasen, no run, very wide outside off, Klaasen looks to cut but misses. It seemed to be outside the wide marker but the umpire stays unmoved. Klaasen not interested in a review either
Thakur to Klaasen, 1 run, short of length outside off, 139.5kph, and Klaasen drags the pull to deep midwicket
There have been just 2 boundaries after the powerplay. Remarkable from CSK
Thakur to Abdul Samad, no run, full and wide outside off, Samad anticipates the line, walks across the stumps and looks to slog. But Thakur goes even wider and beats the edge

Thakur to Abdul Samad, 1 run, short of length outside off, varying it up nicely, and it's flat-batted to long-on. Ruturaj seems to have hurt his finger while fielding and the physio runs out to check on him
Thakur to Klaasen, 1 run, full and wide, Klaasen shuffles across and looks to loft down the ground. But all he manages is a thick inside edge onto pad
Thakur to Abdul Samad, no run, full and very wide outside off, Samad goes chasing and chops it off a thick under-edge to the keeper. Would've been a wide had he left it alone

Summary (Overs 7-15) > Jadeja gets rid of Nitish Reddy > Markram continues to fight for SRH > Pathirana uproots Markram’s middle-stump > Jadeja bowls an economical spell > SRH fail to keep up with the asking rate

Timeout! Required rate is almost 21 and no matter how good Klaasen is, this seems to be beyond him as well. Especially given how well CSK are executing the wide line. They've conceded just 2 boundaries in 9 overs after the powerplay. And to make things even tougher, here's Pathirana again.
109 runs is the lowest score at 15th over mark for SRH in this season
Pathirana starts running in, loses his run-up and aborts. Goes back to his mark
Matheesha Pathirana [1.0-0-8-1] is back into the attack

Pathirana to Klaasen, 1 run, short of length on off, slower one at 127kph and Klaasen is deceived by the lack of pace. He's through the pull shot early and toe-ends it to the right of the keeper. A misfield from Dhoni gives him a single
Pathirana to Abdul Samad, SIX, finally Samad gets hold of one! 140.6kph, right in the slot on off, and he hammers it over long-on
Klaasen has SR 231.5 and Samad has SR 227.3 in death overs (16-20) this season
Pathirana to Abdul Samad, no run, length ball outside off, 138.3kph, Samad looks to cut and chops it down the pitch
Pathirana to Abdul Samad, 1 run, slower bouncer wide of off, Samad reaches out and dabs it to deep third
Pathirana to Klaasen, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Pathirana to Klaasen, out Caught by Mitchell!! Straight down the throat of Mitchell at long-on, and he takes his third catch of the evening. No real fireworks from Klaasen today as he goes for 20 off 21 balls. It's a low full toss on middle, he looks to launch down the ground but fails to get under it. Doesn't get much elevation and it's a comfortable catch. Klaasen c Mitchell b Pathirana 20(21) [6s-1]
Heinrich Klaasen vs Matheesha Pathirana in IPL 8 runs 9 balls two dismissals
Shahbaz Ahmed, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Pathirana to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, full delivery on off, slower one, Shahbaz gets forward and knocks it to extra cover
Pathirana goes off the field with the physio. He seemed to be running in to the crease quite gingerly in that previous over. Let's hope there's no serious issue
Thakur to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, length ball slanted in on middle, Shahbaz works it into the on-side
Thakur to Abdul Samad, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Thakur to Abdul Samad, out Caught by (sub)Sameer Rizvi!! Samad holes out as well! Full and wide outside off, Samad looks to swing down the ground, doesn't get enough and it's catching practice for the substitute fielder at long-off. Abdul Samad c (sub)Sameer Rizvi b Thakur 19(18) [4s-1 6s-1]
Pat Cummins, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Thakur to Cummins, no run, length ball wide of off, Cummins reaches out and tries dabbing it fine but is beaten

Thakur to Cummins, FOUR, full and wide outside off, Cummins throws his bat at it and carves it away through point. Goes very quickly to the boundary. Timing was excellent there, and came right off the middle

Thakur to Cummins, no run, wide not called, and Cummins has reviewed! Replay shows the ball is clearly outside the marker, but Cummins is standing outside off stump to begin with. So the third umpire reckons it's a fair delivery
Thakur to Cummins, 1 run, full and wide, Cummins reaches out and slices it to deep backward point
Tushar Deshpande [2.0-0-23-3] is back into the attack
Tushar Deshpande to Cummins, no run, short of length delivery wide of off, slower one, Cummins tries punching it away but is beaten
Tushar Deshpande to Cummins, no run, slower bouncer outside off, left alone, and there's another review from Cummins for a wide. Is it too high? No, it's passing around the head`
Tushar Deshpande to Cummins, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Tushar Deshpande to Cummins, out Caught by Mitchell!! Fourth catch for Mitchell, and fourth wicket for Deshpande! Fuller than a length, Cummins looks to slog but only hits it as far as long-on. Cummins c Mitchell b Tushar Deshpande 5(7) [4s-1]
Bhuvneshwar Kumar, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Tushar Deshpande to Bhuvneshwar, 1 run, slower bouncer around the head, Bhuvi pulls to deep backward square

Mustafizur Rahman [2.0-0-13-0] is back into the attack
Mustafizur to Shahbaz Ahmed, FOUR, slower bouncer outside off, Shahbaz reaches out and upper-cuts it over short third
Mustafizur to Shahbaz Ahmed, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mustafizur to Shahbaz Ahmed, out Caught by Mitchell!! Mitchell is everywhere! Five catches for him as the ninth wicket goes down! Jaydev Unadkat, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mustafizur to Unadkat, 1 run, taps this through point
Mustafizur to Bhuvneshwar, 1 run, short of length across off, steered to deep third
Mustafizur to Unadkat, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mustafizur to Unadkat, out Caught by Moeen Ali!! All over! Full outside off, Unadkat goes hard on the drive and hits it straight to extra cover. Comfortably held by Moeen, and CSK complete a comprehensive win. Unadkat c Moeen Ali b Mustafizur 1(2)

23:30 Local Time, 18:00 GMT, 23:30 IST: Twice in two games now that SRH have completely fallen apart in a run-chase. They got nowhere close the other day against RCB, and have lost by a massive 78 runs here at Chepauk. CSK will be chuffed with this performance as their bowlers were absolutely remarkable despite there being so much dew on the outfield. They used the reasonably sized square boundaries quite well, especially Deshpande upfront with the new ball as he got both Head and Abhishek caught at deep point. He ended up finishing with his best figures in IPL - going on to take a four-fer, while Pathirana was brilliant again in the middle overs. The execution of plans from the CSK pacers to bowl wide of off after the powerplay, and a brilliant spell of 1/22 from Jadeja, meant that SRH were left deprived of boundaries with even someone like Klaasen struggling to get going. Eventually, most of their batters ended up getting caught in the deep while going for the big shot. They kept finding Mitchell at the boundary, giving him as many as five catches and he held onto every one of those.

Pat Cummins | SRH Captain: (On would he have batted first in hindsight) Not really. We thought it was our best chance to win. They batted well to get to 210 but with thought we were in with a chance with our batting lineup, the pitch was playing well too. We’re pretty happy with how the batting lineup is going. Everyone in that lineup has performed and won us a game at some point in the tournament. It’s definitely dewy now but it was the same in the first innings as well. We’ll bounce back quickly.

Tushar Deshpande: When we came to bowl, the only plan was to have patience against SRH who are quite aggressive in the powerplay and that paid dividends for us. Bowling that length in the powerplay is crucial, even if I get hit, I always challenge the batter to hit that length again and it worked for me today. The ground was soaking wet, it swung for a couple of balls and then it did not. It was a bit sticky and I thought we used the pitch well. We had a specific plan - even if they hit a good ball, we will focus on our plans and not get carried away by them.

150th IPL win as a player for MS Dhoni - first to do so
Stats by Shashikant Singh

Gaikwad, CSK captain and POTM: Feeling pretty good. Tough to play in such wet conditions, and to be able to win by 70-odd runs is a clinical performance. Was blessing in disguise at toss. Everything is good (injury concern?). Too hot and humid conditions. Even the last game, was there batting for 20 overs and fielding for 20 overs. Today also almost same. Wasn't thinking about hundred. Wanted to make sure we get to 220-odd. Was disappointed that I missed 4-5 hits at the back end. During innings break I felt it could make a difference and I was upset. But thankfully it was enough. Last game we made some errors. Some loose balls here and there. Today we were outstanding in the field. Stuck to the plans and knew what the conditions were. With impact player rule, you always want the extra 20 runs. Never know what par score is. That was one area - not getting wickets in powerplay. That's the only way it can put opposition in back foot. He's bowling really well (Deshpande). His hard work is paying off. Special mention to Jaddu as well. In these wet conditions to go for 22 runs, that was the match turning spell. I'm not vocal. Can't tell seniors in the dressing room what to do. You have to take the back seat and let them do their job.

This tournament has really opened up nicely over the last few days. Teams at the top are getting knocked over, and some others in the lower half are making a move. CSK, in fact, have jumped from sixth to third on the table, pushing SRH to fourth. They've bounced back nicely from the defeat against LSG to defend a similar total today, despite there being a lot of dew on the outfield. Execution of plans from all bowlers was brilliant. Two games in a row now that the much vaunted Sunrisers batting lineup has been found wanting in a run-chase. So that's all from us here. It's a goodbye from Sagar Chawla on behalf of Praveen Kumar and Anurag Hegde. Goodnight!
